The paper deals with the manipulation of voting schemes, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The authors also present a general optimization framework for deriving optimal manipulation strategies, which involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper analyzes the impact of manipulation on social welfare, which is a topic in economics and decision theory (cs.EC).
